What is OSS Vendor?

â— So our device has 5 variants.
â— Xiaomi firmware website has all 5 official (firmware+vendor) zip files.
"Always flash your variants vendor."

"Xiaomi never showed us what's in them. Aka closed source"

â— Therefore, some devs decided to make a universal vendor that will work on all variants. Since they are making it. They can optimize it and also always know what's in it.
â— This universal vendor is called OSS vendor. (Open Source Software) (It's not yet perfect though)

â— Some custom ROMs don't include vendor (cause OSS isn't perfect yet)
â— Some custom ROMs include OSS vendor (so we can observe how good it is in daily use)

â— It's always good to know if the rom is using OSS or if we have to flash the official.
â— Currently. Since OSS isn't perfect yet. If the rom doesn't include vendor (or it's a custom miui) do not flash/use OSS with it.

What is OSS Vendor?

â— So our device has 5 variants.
â— Xiaomi firmware website has all 5 official (firmware+vendor) zip files.
"Always flash your variants vendor."

"Xiaomi never showed us what's in them. Aka closed source"

â— Therefore, some devs decided to make a universal vendor that will work on all variants. Since they are making it. They can optimize it and also always know what's in it.
â— This universal vendor is called OSS vendor. (Open Source Software) (It's not yet perfect though)

â— Some custom ROMs don't include vendor (cause OSS isn't perfect yet)
â— Some custom ROMs include OSS vendor (so we can observe how good it is in daily use)

â— It's always good to know if the rom is using OSS or if we have to flash the official.
â— Currently. Since OSS isn't perfect yet. If the rom doesn't include vendor (or it's a custom miui) do not flash/use OSS with it.

What is OSS Vendor?

â— So our device has 5 variants.
â— Xiaomi firmware website has all 5 official (firmware+vendor) zip files.
"Always flash your variants vendor."

"Xiaomi never showed us what's in them. Aka closed source"

â— Therefore, some devs decided to make a universal vendor that will work on all variants. Since they are making it. They can optimize it and also always know what's in it.
â— This universal vendor is called OSS vendor. (Open Source Software) (It's not yet perfect though)

â— Some custom ROMs don't include vendor (cause OSS isn't perfect yet)
â— Some custom ROMs include OSS vendor (so we can observe how good it is in daily use)

â— It's always good to know if the rom is using OSS or if we have to flash the official.
â— Currently. Since OSS isn't perfect yet. If the rom doesn't include vendor (or it's a custom miui) do not flash/use OSS with it.

What is OSS Vendor?

â— So our device has 5 variants.
â— Xiaomi firmware website has all 5 official (firmware+vendor) zip files.
"Always flash your variants vendor."

"Xiaomi never showed us what's in them. Aka closed source"

â— Therefore, some devs decided to make a universal vendor that will work on all variants. Since they are making it. They can optimize it and also always know what's in it.
â— This universal vendor is called OSS vendor. (Open Source Software) (It's not yet perfect though)

â— Some custom ROMs don't include vendor (cause OSS isn't perfect yet)
â— Some custom ROMs include OSS vendor (so we can observe how good it is in daily use)

â— It's always good to know if the rom is using OSS or if we have to flash the official.
â— Currently. Since OSS isn't perfect yet. If the rom doesn't include vendor (or it's a custom miui) do not flash/use OSS with it.

What is OSS Vendor?

â— So our device has 5 variants.
â— Xiaomi firmware website has all 5 official (firmware+vendor) zip files.
"Always flash your variants vendor."

"Xiaomi never showed us what's in them. Aka closed source"

â— Therefore, some devs decided to make a universal vendor that will work on all variants. Since they are making it. They can optimize it and also always know what's in it.
â— This universal vendor is called OSS vendor. (Open Source Software) (It's not yet perfect though)

â— Some custom ROMs don't include vendor (cause OSS isn't perfect yet)
â— Some custom ROMs include OSS vendor (so we can observe how good it is in daily use)

â— It's always good to know if the rom is using OSS or if we have to flash the official.
â— Currently. Since OSS isn't perfect yet. If the rom doesn't include vendor (or it's a custom miui) do not flash/use OSS with it.

What is OSS Vendor?

â— So our device has 5 variants.
â— Xiaomi firmware website has all 5 official (firmware+vendor) zip files.
"Always flash your variants vendor."

"Xiaomi never showed us what's in them. Aka closed source"

â— Therefore, some devs decided to make a universal vendor that will work on all variants. Since they are making it. They can optimize it and also always know what's in it.
â— This universal vendor is called OSS vendor. (Open Source Software) (It's not yet perfect though)

â— Some custom ROMs don't include vendor (cause OSS isn't perfect yet)
â— Some custom ROMs include OSS vendor (so we can observe how good it is in daily use)

â— It's always good to know if the rom is using OSS or if we have to flash the official.
â— Currently. Since OSS isn't perfect yet. If the rom doesn't include vendor (or it's a custom miui) do not flash/use OSS with it.

â— So our device has 5 variants.
â— Xiaomi firmware website has all 5 official (firmware+vendor) zip files.
"Always flash your variants vendor."

"Xiaomi never showed us what's in them. Aka closed source"

â— Therefore, some devs decided to make a universal vendor that will work on all variants. Since they are making it. They can optimize it and also always know what's in it.
â— This universal vendor is called OSS vendor. (Open Source Software) (It's not yet perfect though)

â— Some custom ROMs don't include vendor (cause OSS isn't perfect yet)
â— Some custom ROMs include OSS vendor (so we can observe how good it is in daily use)

â— It's always good to know if the rom is using OSS or if we have to flash the official.
â— Currently. Since OSS isn't perfect yet. If the rom doesn't include vendor (or it's a custom miui) do not flash/use OSS with it.

What is OSS Vendor?

â— So our device has 5 variants.
â— Xiaomi firmware website has all 5 official (firmware+vendor) zip files.
"Always flash your variants vendor."

"Xiaomi never showed us what's in them. Aka closed source"

â— Therefore, some devs decided to make a universal vendor that will work on all variants. Since they are making it. They can optimize it and also always know what's in it.
â— This universal vendor is called OSS vendor. (Open Source Software) (It's not yet perfect though)

â— Some custom ROMs don't include vendor (cause OSS isn't perfect yet)
â— Some custom ROMs include OSS vendor (so we can observe how good it is in daily use)

â— It's always good to know if the rom is using OSS or if we have to flash the official.
â— Currently. Since OSS isn't perfect yet. If the rom doesn't include vendor (or it's a custom miui) do not flash/use OSS with it.

What is OSS Vendor?

â— So our device has 5 variants.
â— Xiaomi firmware website has all 5 official (firmware+vendor) zip files.
"Always flash your variants vendor."

"Xiaomi never showed us what's in them. Aka closed source"

â— Therefore, some devs decided to make a universal vendor that will work on all variants. Since they are making it. They can optimize it and also always know what's in it.
â— This universal vendor is called OSS vendor. (Open Source Software) (It's not yet perfect though)

â— Some custom ROMs don't include vendor (cause OSS isn't perfect yet)
